Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.
result.caption: State of Wisconsin vs. Frank Arnold Tanke Jr

records.addlTxt: Court ordered defendant REMANDED into the custody of the Milwaukee County Sheriff's Department.

Defendant Frank Arnold Tanke Jr not in court, in custody.  Attorney Allison Marie Ritter in court for Frank Arnold Tanke Jr.  Attorney Elaine B. Fehrs in court for State of Wisconsin. Deputy Court Clerk: SD. 
Pretrial Conference held.  Defense raises competency pursuant to Wisc. Stat. 971.14(3).  Court suspends proceedings and ordered defendant be examined by the Forensic Unit.   Defendant remanded into the custody of the Sheriff's Department.  Matter adjourned for Return on Doctor's Report.
Doctor's Report Return scheduled for December 8, 2022 at 01:30 pm.
Received and Filed. Defendant's Motion to Modify Bond
Court is in receipt of defense counsel's motion to adjourn pretrial conference.  Parties emailed new court date.  Case rescheduled for 10/27/2022 at 1:30 pm.
Received and Filed. Defense's Motion to Adjourn

Defendant Frank Arnold Tanke Jr appeared by video, in custody.  Attorney Elaine B. Fehrs appeared by video for State of Wisconsin. Tom Reed appeared on behalf of the Public Defenders Office.
Order to Show Cause Hearing held.  Discussions placed on the record.  Court will adjourn case to allow public defenders office additional time to appoint counsel.  Case adjourned, Br. 41.
Status conference scheduled for October 19, 2022 at 01:30 pm.
Received and Filed. Appointment Status Letter

Defendant Frank Arnold Tanke Jr not in court, in custody.  Prosecuting attorney Abby Rockendorf in court for the State of Wisconsin. 
Case set for status. SPD has not appointed counsel. Court ordered case adjourned for cause to the trial court for a State V. Lee Hearing.
Hearing scheduled for September 27, 2022 at 08:30 am.
Received and Filed. Appointment Status Letter

Defendant Frank Arnold Tanke not in court, defendant in custody at HOC.  Abby Rockendorf appeared in person for the State of Wisconsin.  
Case set for a Preliminary Hearing. State's Witness is present. Case is adjourned. SPD has failed to appoint counsel. Court orders case adjourned for CAUSE for Status of Counsel.  Status conference scheduled for September 8, 2022 at 01:30 pm.
Received and Filed. Appointment Status Letter

Defendant Frank Arnold Tanke not in court, defendant in custody.  Gregg Herman appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  
Case in court for preliminary hearing. OPD needs additional time to appoint an attorney. State requests the matter be set for a State V. Lee hearing or status; denied. Court finds good CAUSE to adjourn preliminary hearing.  Preliminary hearing scheduled for August 15, 2022 at 01:30 pm.

Court ordered no contact with MDW (DOB 08/03/1986)
No Contact/No Weapons Order, signed and filed.
Court ordered defendant TURNED OVER TO Justice Point for SUPERVISION Level 5.  No possession of dangerous weapons or firearms.

Defendant Frank Arnold Tanke in court with attorney Michael V Fuentes.  Defendant Frank Arnold Tanke in custody.  Gregg Herman appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Frank Arnold Tanke appeared by video means with Attorney.  Defendant is advised this case is assigned to Judge Rosa, Branch 35. Parties are advised that effective August 1, 2022 this case will be assigned to Judge Audrey Skwierawski, Branch 41 in Room 501 of the Courthouse.  Defendant given a copy of the complaint and advised of maximum penalties, right to counsel and right to a preliminary hearing.  Court reviewed the complaint and found probable cause to hold the defendant for further proceedings.  DEFENDANT IS INDIGENT AND PUBLIC DEFENDER WILL PROVIDE COUNSEL.   Defense enters a plea of NOT GUILTY as to misdemeanor count(s) 2. Court advised defendant that due to nature of offense in Count 1, a sample of your DNA is required.  If the sheriff's department hasn't already obtained a sample I order them to do so.  There are circumstances that you can request the sample to be expunged from the data base pursuant to statute 165.77(4). This hearing will be streamed live on Dacast:  https://iframe.dacast.com/live/4dafbf46-ed15-c11c-fa22-a58262833632/99073afd-37c2-acfa-830d-b1ddcaebf0ea  Preliminary hearing scheduled for July 18, 2022 at 01:30 pm.
Defendant in Custody, Court appearance today in Intake Court, Room 137A.
